<http://www.uol.com.br/gazetapr/mercosul/mercosulpag2.html#07>
[Abstracted & translated by JW

Paraguay: Dengue has affected 12 000 in the capital
-----------------------------------------------------
The Institute of Tropical Medicine of Assuncion, Paraguay, confirmed 11 600
clinical cases of dengue have been registered in Assuncion alone, but
estimates are that the total for the whole country is more than 100 000.
Ciudad del Este [the city across the Iguassu Falls from Brazil, with
around 30 000 cases, is the most affected.
Brazil
-------
In Foz do Iguacu, the number of dengue cases rose from 39 to 90 last week,
so with 34 imported cases the total is already 124 confirmed, according to
the laboratory of the 9th Health Region. This is the 12th week of the
epidemic in the tri-frontier region [Paraguay, Brazil & Argentina.
Funasa [BrazilÂ´s National Health Foundation staff are fumigating &
larviciding in the frontier municipalities of Paraguay. The Brazilian
government has donated 4 tons of larvicide, enough for 35 days of operations.
